    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Titles that describe what a work is of or about. In art cataloging, descriptive titles are intended to adequately describe what the work is or what the iconography depicted in the work represents. In retrieval, it is designed to be used with other information about the work to uniquely distinguish it from other works in the same results list. </Note_Text>
